{"id":"1807.03467","submitter":"Koji Yamaguchi","authors":"Jose Trevison, Koji Yamaguchi, and Masahiro Hotta","title":"Spatially Overlapped Partners in Quantum Field Theory","comments":"35 pages, 6 figures. Published version","journal-ref":"Journal of Physics A: Mathematical and Theoretical, Volume 52,\n  Number 12 (2019)","doi":"10.1088/1751-8121/ab065b","report-no":null,"categories":"gr-qc hep-th quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In quantum field theory particles are physically defined as what Unruh-DeWitt\nparticle detectors observe. By detecting a particle mode $A$, a reduced density\noperator for a quantum state of $A$ is constructed. Even if the entire quantum\nstate of the quantum field is pure, the state of $A$ is not pure but mixed due\nto entanglement between other subsystems. The partner mode $B$ of the field is\ndefined as a purification partner of $A$ such that the $AB$ system in a pure\nstate. We show that, without any fine-tuning of the particle detector design of\n$A$, the weighting function of partner $B$ has spatial overlap of that of $A$.\nWe show a general formula of partner $B$ associated with arbitrarily fixed $A$\nof a free field in a general Gaussian state. We demonstrate an example of\nmemory effects in an expanding Freedman-Roberson-Walker universe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Jul 2018 03:35:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 19 Sep 2018 06:51:46 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 4 Oct 2018 01:15:30 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 19 Dec 2018 05:12:11 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Fri, 1 Mar 2019 04:18:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-04"}
